The paper focuses on designing a new architecture for graph convolutional networks (GCNs) that overcomes the oversmoothness problem caused by previous architectures. This problem is related to the representation of local graph structures and the multiscale nature of graph data. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
